      "content": "Eugenicists claimed that the physical characteristics of darker-skinned groups, such as a larger head, a flat face, and a \"sloping\" skull, were indicative of a lower genetic quality. They argued that these physical traits were linked to a supposed decline in intelligence, moral character, and social behavior. For example, they claimed that the \"sloping\" skull was a sign of a \"degenerate\" brain, and that the larger head size was a sign of a \"savage\" or \"uncivilized\" mind. They also linked darker skin to a supposed increase in \"moral\" and \"emotional\" traits, such as \"passion\" and \"impulsiveness,\" which they believed were inferior to the supposedly more \"rational\" and \"civilized\" traits of lighter-skinned groups. This supposed link between physical characteristics and social behavior was often based on flawed assumptions and a complete disregard for the complexities of human genetics and the impact of environmental factors on human development.",
